question:
Let S be the set of all values of a1 for which the mean deviation about the mean of 100 consecutive positive integers a1, a2, a3, ..., a100 is 25. Then S is:
(1) {9}
(2) {99}
(3) empty set
(4) N (all natural numbers)

If domain of f(x) = [x]/(1+x^2), where [x] is greatest integer <= x, is [2,6), then its range is:
(1) [5/37, 2/5]
(2) [5/37, 2/5] - {9/29, 27/109, 18/89, 9/53}
(3) [5/26, 2/5]
(4) [5/26, 2/5] - {9/29, 27/109, 18/89, 9/53}
